WEBVTT

00:04.326 --> 00:07.089
So, Eric, your dad's
muffler shop opens tomorrow.

00:07.141 --> 00:11.479
That's, like, the perfect job for him.
I mean, he's been muffling you for years.

00:12.125 --> 00:14.397
Yes, he really hates noise.

00:14.474 --> 00:17.439
I think it's because
it reminds him of fun.

00:17.736 --> 00:21.076
Hey, at least Red got a job he likes.
I thought I was cool flipping burgers,

00:21.157 --> 00:26.576
then I met the night shift guy who's been doing it for 30
years. He's got no eyebrows, and he lives in his own car.

00:27.806 --> 00:29.789
I don't want to be that guy.

00:29.939 --> 00:33.306
And you won't be if you
follow the plan I gave you,

00:33.356 --> 00:35.772
Okay? We get a job
as a local weather team,

00:35.822 --> 00:38.089
then go national as
morning talk show hosts,

00:38.122 --> 00:41.756
and then... star in
our own ice capades.

00:42.872 --> 00:46.059
Jackie, I've told you,
I don't capade.

00:46.609 --> 00:48.959
- I am quitting my job, though.
- Me too.

00:49.009 --> 00:52.709
The department of motor vehicles
is not as glamorous as it sounds.

00:53.892 --> 00:55.792
You know what
motor vehicles are?

00:56.059 --> 00:57.576
They're cars.

01:00.126 --> 01:02.381
Just cars.

01:04.048 --> 01:07.681
Fez, you know what you should do?
You should be a cop like me.

01:07.731 --> 01:10.398
You could go undercover
and catch foreigners.

01:15.315 --> 01:17.881
Oh, so it's a crime
to be foreign, huh?

01:18.648 --> 01:20.265
No, of course not.

01:20.298 --> 01:23.348
It's a crime to do the
things that foreigners do.

01:23.881 --> 01:27.615
Well, I, for one, love my
job. Want to know why?

01:27.665 --> 01:29.432
I have no job.

01:29.515 --> 01:32.132
Yeah, that's one of the
benefits of taking the year off.

01:32.198 --> 01:35.532
Speaking of that, how'd that all-day
marathon go on the slip 'n slide?

01:35.865 --> 01:37.515
Pretty good.

01:37.998 --> 01:40.615
Except for around
hour three, when...

01:40.815 --> 01:42.882
I got a pretty
serious owie.

01:43.265 --> 01:47.182
Yeah, when you went in for a juice,
I slipped a rock under there.

01:48.198 --> 01:51.931
Ah. Anyway, today, I
will be chasing butterflies.

01:52.665 --> 01:56.015
Tomorrow, I'm gonna break
out the giant bubble wand.

01:56.581 --> 01:59.931
What'd you do, go down the
clearance aisle at the drugstore?

02:00.548 --> 02:02.098
Yes, I did.

02:02.614 --> 02:06.764
You'll all be happy to know you'll be receiving
goody bags containing 4th of July socks,

02:06.797 --> 02:08.146
cornstarch

02:08.197 --> 02:10.564
and a calendar
from 1972.

02:15.659 --> 02:18.509
Okay, I think we're nearly
set up for business.

02:18.542 --> 02:20.742
Thanks for helping,
or, uh,

02:20.775 --> 02:23.992
standing around saying,
"ew, grease."

02:24.142 --> 02:26.225
Whoa, Steven.

02:26.292 --> 02:27.975
You already got
that muffler together?

02:28.009 --> 02:31.309
Yeah, well, you know, metal
shop was my favorite class.

02:31.492 --> 02:32.725
I went to, like,

02:32.759 --> 02:34.342
half of 'em.

02:36.292 --> 02:39.542
You know, I need an extra set of hands
around here. How'd you like the job?

02:39.592 --> 02:41.259
No, Steven, you can't.

02:41.292 --> 02:46.625
I mean, don't take this personally, Mr. Forman, but
guys who work in muffler shops are bottom-feeders.

02:46.858 --> 02:47.892
Jackie.

02:47.942 --> 02:51.692
Well, I said, "don't take this
personally." What else can I do?

02:52.458 --> 02:54.892
Jackie, I gotta take
this job. You kidding me?

02:54.925 --> 02:57.725
I mean, I'm good with
my hands, I don't mind dirt,

02:57.775 --> 03:00.425
and I have a high
tolerance for fumes.

03:01.508 --> 03:04.108
Fine. If it makes you
happy, then I'm happy.

03:04.158 --> 03:08.591
Steven, why is it everything that I
love about you also grosses me out?

03:08.975 --> 03:10.775
You're so complicated.

03:10.925 --> 03:13.508
Okay. You can
start tomorrow.

03:13.708 --> 03:16.691
But we're not driving in
together. That's too weird.

03:17.441 --> 03:18.541
Cool.

03:19.051 --> 03:21.235
All right, I gotta take off. I'm gonna
go have lunch with my new dad.

03:21.285 --> 03:23.418
Oh, bring a camera
get a picture.

03:23.468 --> 03:25.835
Steven, you don't have
any family pictures.

03:25.918 --> 03:29.468
Well, we have some really good ones
of my mom down at the county jail.

03:30.901 --> 03:34.484
One full face, two profiles--
each one dated and numbered.

03:34.918 --> 03:37.751
Oh, Steven, you've
had the hardest life.

03:37.968 --> 03:40.785
You know, I should probably be more
generous and considerate with you.

03:40.835 --> 03:42.635
But I am
what I am.

03:43.951 --> 03:49.042
Okay, we are going to make this
the prettiest muffler shop ever.

03:50.626 --> 03:53.326
Really, all I wanted was
a "grand opening" sign.

03:53.376 --> 03:55.742
And you've got one...

03:56.576 --> 03:58.742
in needlepoint.

04:02.063 --> 04:03.813
Kitty that's so tiny.

04:03.847 --> 04:05.947
Needlepoint is
very hard work.

04:05.997 --> 04:08.213
You never appreciate
anything I do.

04:08.247 --> 04:10.647
You should've just
married Betty Parker.

04:12.047 --> 04:14.963
No, no, no. What I meant
was, it's so tiny, like...

04:15.213 --> 04:16.762
your waist.

04:17.163 --> 04:19.096
Thank you.

04:20.346 --> 04:22.230
Eric, you want to
hand me that manifold?

04:22.297 --> 04:24.063
The manifold.

04:31.563 --> 04:34.780
Mani... fold.

04:36.463 --> 04:40.263
Man, I folded that.

04:40.930 --> 04:43.448
Eric, are you ready
to help me decorate?

04:43.497 --> 04:48.013
Yes, now I was thinking we could line this
counter here with red-white-and-blue bunting.

04:48.813 --> 04:54.121
How is it that I raised a son who
knows "bunting" but not "manifold"?

04:55.588 --> 04:59.071
Well, maybe the problem is
that you were never around.

04:59.521 --> 05:01.921
I was always around.

05:04.471 --> 05:06.354
Yeah, maybe I
was the problem.

